Product Management OS: System Architecture & Workflows
Part 1: System Modules & Capabilities

The OS is divided into seven core modules, each housing specific processing engines to handle different phases of the product lifecycle.

1. Discovery Mode

    user-interview-analyzer: Transforms raw interview transcripts into structured snapshots and opportunities.

    research-synthesis-engine: Combines insights from multiple research sources to find patterns and themes.

    jtbd-extractor: Reframes raw research into actionable Jobs-to-be-Done statements.

    user-journey-mapper: Maps out the user's emotional state, touchpoints, and friction.

    opportunity-solution-tree: Maps business outcomes to user needs and testable solutions.

2. Strategy Mode

    landscape-mapper: Maps multiple competitors to identify market gaps and strategic groups.

    competitive-profile-builder: Analyzes a specific competitor's strengths, moats, and business sustainability using the DHM framework.

    swot-analysis-generator: Creates a structured SWOT and actionable TOWS matrix.

    positioning-statement-generator: Uses the "Obviously Awesome" framework to define market category and unique value.

    pricing-strategy-analyzer: Evaluates pricing models, packaging, and revenue impacts.

3. Plan Mode

    north-star-finder: Identifies the single core metric that captures the product's value delivery.

    cogs-analyzer: Evaluates unit economics, infrastructure costs, and basic P&L tracking.

    tech-debt-evaluator: Quantifies the business cost of bad architecture to justify engineering-led refactoring initiatives.

    quarterly-planning-template: Defines strategic themes, bets, resource allocation, and a "NOT doing" list.

    roadmap-builder: Links initiatives to business objectives and sets Now/Next/Later timelines.

4. Priority Mode

    backlog-prioritizer: Triages and groups larger backlogs (10+ items) into P0-P3 buckets using RICE and strategic overrides.

    prioritization-engine: Scores and defends 3+ roadmap features using RICE, ICE, or Value/Effort frameworks.

5. Feature & Specs Mode

    prd-generator: Structures messy ideas into PRDs containing success criteria, dependencies, and risk assessments.

    technical-spec-writer: Translates PRDs into engineering specs covering architecture, data models, and API endpoints.

    user-story-writer: Breaks features down into sprint-ready stories using the INVEST criteria and BDD acceptance criteria.

6. Data Mode

    ab-test-designer: Designs statistically sound experiments with hypotheses, sample sizes, and guardrail metrics.

7. Productivity Mode

    weekly-plan: Connects the week's top 3-5 priorities to quarterly goals and flags risks.

    daily-plan: Time-blocks the day for focus work and meetings while aligning to top priorities.

Part 2: Integrated OS Workflows

To create a true "Operating System," these tools must pass data to one another. Here are four high-value workflows combining these capabilities.
Workflow A: Zero-to-One Product Discovery

Goal: Take a vague market opportunity and turn it into a validated, testable solution.

    user-interview-analyzer processes initial customer conversations.

    research-synthesis-engine aggregates these interviews into core themes.

    jtbd-extractor converts these themes into specific Jobs-to-be-Done.

    user-journey-mapper identifies exactly where in the current workflow the user experiences the most friction trying to achieve those jobs.

    opportunity-solution-tree takes the friction points and maps out potential solutions tied to a target business outcome.

Workflow B: Quarterly Strategic Planning Loop

Goal: Align the company on what to build next quarter based on market realities and business constraints.

    north-star-finder re-establishes the core metric to move for the upcoming quarter.

    landscape-mapper & competitive-profile-builder analyze recent competitor movements to identify defensive or offensive needs.

    tech-debt-evaluator & cogs-analyzer review internal health to decide how much capacity must be allocated to maintenance versus new features.

    quarterly-planning-template synthesizes market needs and internal health into strategic themes and a strict "NOT doing" list.

    roadmap-builder generates the Now/Next/Later visualization for stakeholder alignment.

Workflow C: The "Idea to Sprint" Execution Pipeline

Goal: Take an approved roadmap initiative and break it down into engineering-ready tasks.

    prioritization-engine selects the highest ROI feature from the "Now" column of the roadmap.

    prd-generator drafts the comprehensive requirements and constraints.

    ab-test-designer hooks into the PRD to define exactly how the feature's success will be measured at launch.

    technical-spec-writer digests the PRD and outputs the architecture/data requirements for engineering review.

    user-story-writer breaks the technical and product requirements into granular, sprint-ready Jira/Linear tickets.

Workflow D: Go-to-Market & Commercialization

Goal: Ensure a new feature or product is positioned and priced to win in the market.

    swot-analysis-generator assesses the product's current standing against alternatives.

    positioning-statement-generator creates the external messaging and defines the exact market category.

    pricing-strategy-analyzer determines how to monetize this new value (e.g., freemium, add-on, usage-based) based on the positioning.

    weekly-plan & daily-plan ensure the PM allocates dedicated time to coordinate the launch with Sales and Marketing.